explanation_txt:

quest_title: 100ml 10% KOH is mixed with 100ml 10% \(\text{H\({}_{2}\)SO\({}_{4}\)}\) the resulting solution is
explanation_txt:
For same mass of KOH and H\(_2\)SO\(_4\),

Normality \(\propto \cfrac{1}{\text{Equivalent Weight}}\)

\(\cfrac{\text{Normality of KOH}}{\text{Normality of H\(_2\)SO\(_4\)}}\) = \(\cfrac{\text{Equivalent weight of H\(_2\)SO\(_4\)}}{\text{Equivalent weight of KOH}}\) = \(\cfrac{49}{56}\) = \(\cfrac{7}{8}\) 

Since normality of KOH is less than that of H\(_2\)SO\(_4\), the solution is acidic.
